Protonymph. Podonotal region ( figure 6C ) with single weakly defined plate and weakly sclerotized mesonotal and pygidial regions. Setae z1 , s2–3 , 5 ; J1 , Z1–2 ; S2 ; and r-R series setae added; seta j2 apparently not added. Fixed digit with excrescence, paraxial lobe, five to six small teeth, and a large basal tooth. Subcapitulum with four pairs of setae. Intercoxal shield with three pairs of setae;
